The paper deals with auctions for digital goods, which is a topic related to game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.EC). The use of probabilistic techniques and dynamic programming suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the analysis of competitive ratios involves information theory (cs.IT).
